# Project 006 — Acceptance Testing

## Date

2026-07-24

## Category

QA Testing

## Difficulty

Advanced

## Focus

User Acceptance Testing (UAT), Business Requirement Validation, Release Readiness

---

# Objective

Perform User Acceptance Testing (UAT) on a completed feature to determine whether it satisfies the defined business requirements and is ready for production release.

---

# Scenario

A task management application has introduced a **Task Assignment** feature.

The product owner requests User Acceptance Testing before deployment.

---

# Business Requirements

The feature must allow users to:

- Assign tasks to existing team members.
- Update task ownership.
- Notify the assigned user.
- Display the assignee on the task details page.
- Restrict task assignment to project members only.

---

# Evaluation Criteria

| Criteria | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| Requirement Validation | Are business requirements satisfied? |
| User Experience | Can users complete the workflow easily? |
| Functionality | Does the feature work as expected? |
| Documentation | Are results recorded clearly? |
| Release Readiness | Is the feature suitable for production? |

---

